Reading the other reviews, thinking maybe this place has a takeout/delivery problem, although I have no idea how the reviews for the food in the restaurant and what we received could come out of the same kitchen. Simply stated, if I'm ordering Thai food, I'm ordering it because I want food with flavor.  Sorry to say, considering how I always want to support local businesses, that this was unfortunately the blandest and most flavorless Thai food I've ever had, and I've ordered from Spice in Manhattan. Som Tum was lacking that signature blend of fish sauce, lime juice, sugar, and spice. Just a lot of chiles and cardboard tasting green papaya. Pad thai was nothing but noodles and chicken, overly sweet, dry and...well..pretty much flavorless. No fried tofu, 4 little bits of green onion, and...that's it. Tom yum soup was in comparison good, but still watery.  If a Thai restaurant can't nail these simple staples (also tasted the wife's order of Tom kha and drunken noodles, same conclusion:  flavorless except for overly sugary, which, drunken noodles? Sweet?) then just order from somewhere else. Outside of Sunnyside/Elmhurst Queens, NYC seems to have a serious dearth of quality Thai places, and unfortunately this seems to fall into the category of "just not making it".
